entry.title: Suppress LSI updates when adding host_window as widget_ child
entry.content:
Two things are going on with this bug:



1. AddChild involves propagating a non-1 device_scale_factor to

`host_window()` and it triggers `host_window()` to advance its

`LocalSurfaceId`. Changing device_scale_factor this way does not send

configure events.



2. On the first commit, `host_window()->layer()` doesn't have a

`LocalSurfaceId`, and we force it to take `host_window()`'s LSI to

proceed.



As a result, if no configure events are sent after this

device_scale_factor change the `commit_target_layer` cannot be found

b/c neither `old_layer`s nor `host_window()->layer()` has the same

`parent_sequence_number` as `surface_tree_host`'s LSI.



Solution: suppress LSI update when we establish parent-child.



Bug: 1505583

entry.title: [blink] Change GMBImageCopy::CopyImage() to pass back GMBHandle
entry.content:
As a first step toward converting GpuMemoryBufferImageCopy to use

Mappable SharedImage rather than GpuMemoryBuffer, this CL internalizes

its usage of its GMB by changing its CopyImage() method to pass back a

GMBHandle rather than the GMB. The one caller of this method only uses

the GMB to get the handle.



Note: This CL changes the caller from checking for an error via the

passed in GMB pointer being null to checking for the error via

GMBHandle::is_null() being true. This check is semantically equivalent

because the GMB is created via

ClientGMBManager::CreateGpuMemoryBuffer(), which returns nullptr if

is_null() returns true on the backing handle [1]; hence, when the

GMBImageCopy's GMB is non-null, is_null() is guaranteed to be false on

entry.title: [editing] Fix triple-clicking a contenteditable next to a non-contenteditable doesn't select the whole paragraph
entry.content:
Consider this test case:



Paragraph 1




Paragraph 2








Triple-clicking div#one which is next to a non-contenteditable element,

`new_selection` is returned by `ExpandWithGranularity`.

The value `new_selection.Extent()` is `div#two@offsetInAnchor[0]`.

Since div#two is non-editable, `VisiblePosition` of

`new_selection.Extent()` is null.

`CanonicalizeSelection` return a caret selection. In this case,

triple-clicking from the user's perspective will not select anything.



`AdjustSelectionToAvoidCrossingEditingBoundaries` ensures selection

not crossing editing boundaries, but `AdjustSelectionType` returned

the wrong result. It will call `MostForward/BackwardCaretPosition`

on `Extent/Base`, this will result in the `VisiblePosition` of

the selection will be the caret. In this case, we shouldn't

forward/backward the start/end position of `range`.



Bug: 1371268

entry.title: Prerender: Propagate new tab trigger cancellation to initiator WC
entry.content:
The cancellation of new-tab hosts can be invoked through either the

initiator WebContentss PrerenderHostRegistry or PHR on WC created for

new-tab hosts. This CL propagates latter cancellation to initiator WCs

PHR to perform the followings:

- Clear the corresponding entry of

prerender_new_tab_handle_by_frame_tree_node_id_ in the initiator PHR.

This will eventually destroy WC created for new-tab hosts.

- Notify the initiator PrerendererImpl of cancellation (for consistency)



This CL implements this by asynchronously calling initiator PHRs

CancelNewTabHostInternal on the CancelHostInternal on the new-tab PHR.

For more information, please refer to this doc:

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1JSVM-Q03rsn9bAzlRdLsA_FMjPeJTI8KonEjorX27Xo

entry.title: Reland "Dispatch close event when MessagePort is disentangled"
entry.content:
This is a reland of commit 6a74d3d8049e1744b862757a73f90f3d7a5e08b0



The tests newly added by the original CL were failing on

chrome_wpt_tests on the Linux Tests bot:

https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chromium/builders/ci/Linux%20Tests/138259/overview



This is because the builder added in https://crrev.com/c/5005230 might be broken.

Specifically, chrome-wpt builder cannot run GC(Bug: 1509657) and BFCache doesn't

work on chrome-wpt builder(Bug: 1509303).



I changed two tests expectations described below.

third_party/blink/web_tests/external/wpt/webmessaging/message-channels/close-event/garbage-collected.tentative.any.js



third_party/blink/web_tests/external/wpt/html/browsers/browsing-the-web/back-forward-cache/message-port-entangled-after-restore.https.tentative.window.js



Original change's description:

> Dispatch close event when MessagePort is disentangled

>

> We want to dispatch a close event when an entangled MessagePort is disconnected.

> Given a pair of entangled ports, port1 and port2, if port2 is closed at any point,

> a port1s error handler is run.

> So we can change an error handler to dispatch a close event.

>

> The tests of close event are as follows:

> 1) port was explicitly closed.

> 2) owning document was destroyed.

> 3) owning document crashed.

> 4) port was garbage collected.

>

> Design Doc:https://docs.google.com/document/d/1lXZU2Pk2ycitqj8aL9kxT2aauwXqpA0vJDUalkXA29Y

entry.title: Make shelf app icon > "New window" send NEW_WINDOW launch disposition
entry.content:
This CL updates the "New window" shelf app menu item to launch with

a NEW_WINDOW disposition.



This helps to fix a bug in tabbed web apps:

When picking "new window" for tabbed web apps nothing would happen.

Under the hood a new tab in an existing was being opened at the

start_url, this matched the home tab scope and the navigation would

get captured by the pinned home tab, closing the new tab.

By making the intention of the user explicit, tabbed web apps can now

launch a separate window in this scenario.



Before: https://bugs.chromium.org/p/chromium/issues/attachment?aid=620764&signed_aid=kSzUs3ZqRLYy44GPFsvCGw==&inline=1

After: https://bugs.chromium.org/p/chromium/issues/attachment?aid=620763&signed_aid=aiBn73PpUSd3NzwBTHUliQ==&inline=1



Regarding existing code paths:

This change affects all app types. Having researched the use of

AppLaunchParams::disposition there are no dependencies on the

NEW_WINDOW disposition that would be affected across all app types.

https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:chrome/browser/apps/app_service/app_launch_params.h?q=symbol:%5Cbapps::AppLaunchParams::disposition%5Cb%20case:yes

and for the PlatformSpellCheckEngine. An opaque tag was passed

renderer to the browser.

wasn't used correctly. Each SpellCheckHostChromeImpl gets its own
